The paper analyzes the content and effects of a specific online forum, which falls under the category of social media. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves data analysis and measurement, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Geometry), cs.SD (Software Engineering), or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper touches on hate speech and online harassment, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as it involves analyzing the complexity of social interactions.
